other_tests.findings: The patient has acute appendicitis with a large dilated appendix measuring 1.6 cm, adjacent fat stranding, and an appendicolith. There is no free air or abscess or fluid collection, but there are multiple enhancing periappendiceal nodes compatible with reactive adenopathy. There is a small amount of free fluid in the pelvis. Rectum, sigmoid colon, urinary bladder are unremarkable.
